fuzzing_params.Constraints: 1 <= words.length <= 100, 1 <= words[i].length <= 5 * 10^3. The input is generated such that sum(words[i].length) <= 10^5. words[i] consists only of lowercase English letters. 1 <= target.length <= 5 * 10^3. target consists only of lowercase English letters.

problem_info.title: 3291. Minimum Number of Valid Strings to Form Target I
problem_info.test_examples:
Example 1:
Input: words = ["abc","aaaaa","bcdef"], target = "aabcdabc"
Output: 3
Explanation:
The target string can be formed by concatenating:
Prefix of length 2 of words[1], i.e. "aa".
Prefix of length 3 of words[2], i.e. "bcd".
Prefix of length 3 of words[0], i.e. "abc".
Example 2:
Input: words = ["abababab","ab"], target = "ababaababa"
Output: 2
Explanation:
The target string can be formed by concatenating:
Prefix of length 5 of words[0], i.e. "ababa".
Prefix of length 5 of words[0], i.e. "ababa".
